### API Testing for Project Management Backend
### Make sure your server is running on http://localhost:3000

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = your_jwt_token_here

### 1. First, you need to login to get a token (assuming you have auth endpoints)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "your_email@example.com",
  "password": "your_password"
}

### 2. Create a Workspace
POST {{baseUrl}}/workspace
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{token}}

{
  "name": "My Test Workspace"
}

### 3. Get User Workspaces
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspace
Cookie: token={{token}}

### 4. Create a Board (replace workspaceId with actual ID from step 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/boards
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{token}}

{
  "name": "My Test Board",
  "workspaceId": "WORKSPACE_ID_HERE"
}

### 5. Get Workspace Boards (replace workspaceId with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/boards/WORKSPACE_ID_HERE
Cookie: token={{token}}

### 6. Create a List (replace boardId with actual ID from step 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/lists
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{token}}

{
  "name": "To Do",
  "boardId": "BOARD_ID_HERE"
}

### 7. Get Board Lists (replace boardId with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/lists/BOARD_ID_HERE
Cookie: token={{token}}

### 8. Create another List
POST {{baseUrl}}/lists
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{token}}

{
  "name": "In Progress",
  "boardId": "BOARD_ID_HERE"
}

### 9. Create third List
POST {{baseUrl}}/lists
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: token={{token}}

{
  "name": "Done",
  "boardId": "BOARD_ID_HERE"
}